{"title_page": "Gabriela Firea", "text_new": "{{Infobox officeholder\n|name        = Gabriela Firea\n|image       = Gabriela Firea la sediul PSD - 14 (1) (15011046688).jpg\n|office      = [[Mayor of Bucharest]]\n|term_start  = 23 June 2016\n|term_end    = \n|predecessor = R\u0103zvan Sava (Acting)\n|successor   = \n|birth_date  = {{birth date and age|1972|7|13|df=y}}\n|birth_place = [[Bac\u0103u]], [[Romania]]\n|death_date  = \n|death_place = \n|party       = [[Social Democratic Party (Romania)|Social Democratic Party]]\n|spouse      = [https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/Florentin_Pandele Florentin Pandele] \n}}\n'''Gabriela Firea''' (born '''Gabriela Vr\u00e2nceanu''', 13 July 1972) is a [[Romania]]n journalist and politician who currently serves as mayor of [[Bucharest]].\n\nBorn in [[Bac\u0103u]], she has worked in radio, newspapers and television,<ref name=\"sim\">{{in lang|ro}} Anca Simionescu, [http://www.evz.ro/gabriela-vranceanu-firea-pandele-este-singurul-barbat-idem-cu-mine-964760.html \"Gabriela Vr\u00e2nceanu Firea: 'Pandele este singurul b\u0103rbat idem cu mine'\"], ''Evenimentul Zilei'', February 5, 2012</ref> including as a [[news presenter]].<ref>{{in lang|ro}} [http://adevarul.ro/entertainment/celebritati/gabriela-vranceanu-fireaprezentatoare-tv-prefer-fiu-invidiata-decat-compatimita-1_50ad48ed7c42d5a66392405c/index.html \"Gabriela Vr\u00e2nceanu Firea,prezentatoare TV: 'Prefer s\u0103 fiu invidiat\u0103 dec\u00e2t comp\u0103timit\u0103'\"], ''Adev\u0103rul'', November 16, 2011</ref> A member of the [[Social Democratic Party (Romania)|Social Democratic Party]], she was elected to the [[Romanian Senate]] [[2012 Romanian legislative election|in 2012]] for an [[Ilfov County]] seat. She sat on the Senate's culture committee.<ref>{{in lang|ro}} [http://www.cdep.ro/pls/parlam/structura.mp?idm=66&leg=2012&cam=1 2012- profile] at the Romanian Chamber of Deputies site</ref> She had a difficult childhood because the man she loved dumped her for being too poor.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://revistatango.ro/gabriela-vranceanu-firea-baiatul-pe-care-l-iubeam-m-a-parasit-pentru-ca-eram-prea-saraca-1019|title=GABRIELA VRANCEANU FIREA: Baiatul pe care-l iubeam m-a parasit pentru ca eram prea saraca \u2013 Marea Dragoste|work=Marea Dragoste|access-date=2018-05-23|language=ro-RO}}</ref>\n\nShe married R\u0103svan Firea in 1993 and the couple had one son. One year after R\u0103svan's death in 2010, she married Florentin Pandele,<ref name=\"sim\"/> the mayor of [[Voluntari]].<ref>{{in lang|ro}} [http://adevarul.ro/news/bucuresti/florentin-pandele-despre-relatia-amoroasa-gabriela-vranceanu-firea-da-iubesc-cerut-o-casatorie-gabi-1_50bde91e7c42d5a663cfc940/index.html \"Florentin Pandele, despre rela\u0163ia amoroas\u0103 cu Gabriela Vr\u00e2nceanu Firea\"], ''Adev\u0103rul'', September 6, 2010</ref> They have two sons.<ref>{{in lang|ro}} [http://www.mediafax.ro/life-inedit/senatoarea-psd-gabriela-firea-a-nascut-cel-de-al-treilea-baietel-pe-care-il-va-chema-zian-mihail-foto-14210736 \"Senatoarea PSD Gabriela Firea a n\u0103scut cel de-al treilea b\u0103ie\u0163el\"], Mediafax, May 5, 2015</ref>\n\nAt the [[2016 Romanian local election|June 2016 local election]], Firea was elected the first female mayor of Bucharest.<ref>{{in lang|ro}} Ana Maria Laz\u0103r, [http://www.mediafax.ro/politic/gabriela-firea-prima-femeie-primar-a-capitalei-dupa-doar-4-ani-de-cariera-politica-foto-15453280 \"Gabriela Firea \u2013 prima femeie primar a Capitalei dup\u0103 doar 4 ani de carier\u0103 politic\u0103\"], Mediafax, June 8, 2016</ref> She won 43% from the total of only 33% that went to vote. Her closest challengers, [[Nicu\u0219or Dan]] ([[Save Bucharest Union]]) and [[C\u0103t\u0103lin Predoiu]] ([[National Liberal Party (Romania)|National Liberal Party]]), won 30.5% and 11.2% respectively.<ref>{{in lang|ro}} Roxana Preda, [http://www.mediafax.ro/politic/rezultate-finale-alegeri-locale-2016-gabriela-firea-42-97-nicusor-dan-30-52-catalin-predoiu-11-18-toate-contestatiile-respinse-15467482 \"Rezultate finale alegeri locale 2016\"], Mediafax, June 10, 2016</ref>\n\n==Electoral history==\n===Mayor of Bucharest===\n{| class=wikitable width=100%\n! rowspan=2|Election\n! rowspan=2|Affiliation\n! colspan=3|First round\n! colspan=3|Second round\n|-\n!Votes\n!Percentage\n!Position\n!Votes\n!Percentage\n!Position\n|-align=center\n! [[2016 Romanian local election|2016]]\n| {{yes2|'''[[Social Democratic Party (Romania)|PSD]]'''}} || 246,553 || {{Percentage bar|42.97|c={{Social Democratic Party (Romania)/meta/color}}}} || {{color box|Gold|1st}} || bgcolor=lightgrey colspan=3|\n|}\n\n\n==Notes==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|Gabriela Firea}}\n*{{in lang|ro}} [http://gabriela-firea.ro Official site]\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Firea, Gabriela}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1972 births]]\n[[Category:People from Bac\u0103u]]\n[[Category:Members of the Romanian Orthodox Church]]\n[[Category:Romanian journalists]]\n[[Category:Romanian television presenters]]\n[[Category:Social Democratic Party (Romania) politicians]]\n[[Category:Mayors of Bucharest]]\n[[Category:Members of the Senate of Romania]]\n[[Category:Romanian women in politics]]\n[[Category:Women television presenters]]\n[[Category:Spouses of mayors]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox officeholder\n|name        = Gabriela Firea\n|image       = Gabriela Firea la sediul PSD - 14 (1) (15011046688).jpg\n|office      = [[Mayor of Bucharest]]\n|term_start  = 23 June 2016\n|term_end    = \n|predecessor = R\u0103zvan Sava (Acting)\n|successor   = \n|birth_date  = {{birth date and age|1972|7|13|df=y}}\n|birth_place = [[Bac\u0103u]], [[Romania]]\n|death_date  = \n|death_place = \n|party       = [[Social Democratic Party (Romania)|Social Democratic Party]]\n|spouse      = [https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/Florentin_Pandele Florentin Pandele] \n}}\n'''Gabriela Firea''' (born '''Gabriela Vr\u00e2nceanu''', 13 July 1972) is a [[Romania]]n journalist and politician who currently serves as mayor of [[Bucharest]].\n\nBorn in [[Bac\u0103u]], she has worked in radio, newspapers and television,<ref name=\"sim\">{{in lang|ro}} Anca Simionescu, [http://www.evz.ro/gabriela-vranceanu-firea-pandele-este-singurul-barbat-idem-cu-mine-964760.html \"Gabriela Vr\u00e2nceanu Firea: 'Pandele este singurul b\u0103rbat idem cu mine'\"], ''Evenimentul Zilei'', February 5, 2012</ref> including as a [[news presenter]].<ref>{{in lang|ro}} [http://adevarul.ro/entertainment/celebritati/gabriela-vranceanu-fireaprezentatoare-tv-prefer-fiu-invidiata-decat-compatimita-1_50ad48ed7c42d5a66392405c/index.html \"Gabriela Vr\u00e2nceanu Firea,prezentatoare TV: 'Prefer s\u0103 fiu invidiat\u0103 dec\u00e2t comp\u0103timit\u0103'\"], ''Adev\u0103rul'', November 16, 2011</ref> A member of the [[Social Democratic Party (Romania)|Social Democratic Party]], she was elected to the [[Romanian Senate]] [[2012 Romanian legislative election|in 2012]] for an [[Ilfov County]] seat. She sat on the Senate's culture committee.<ref>{{in lang|ro}} [http://www.cdep.ro/pls/parlam/structura.mp?idm=66&leg=2012&cam=1 2012- profile] at the Romanian Chamber of Deputies site</ref> She had a difficult childhood because the man she loved dumped her for being too poor.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://revistatango.ro/gabriela-vranceanu-firea-baiatul-pe-care-l-iubeam-m-a-parasit-pentru-ca-eram-prea-saraca-1019|title=GABRIELA VRANCEANU FIREA: Baiatul pe care-l iubeam m-a parasit pentru ca eram prea saraca \u2013 Marea Dragoste|work=Marea Dragoste|access-date=2018-05-23|language=ro-RO}}</ref>\n\nShe married R\u0103zvan Firea in 1993 and the couple had one son. One year after R\u0103zvan's death in 2010, she married Florentin Pandele,<ref name=\"sim\"/> the mayor of [[Voluntari]].<ref>{{in lang|ro}} [http://adevarul.ro/news/bucuresti/florentin-pandele-despre-relatia-amoroasa-gabriela-vranceanu-firea-da-iubesc-cerut-o-casatorie-gabi-1_50bde91e7c42d5a663cfc940/index.html \"Florentin Pandele, despre rela\u0163ia amoroas\u0103 cu Gabriela Vr\u00e2nceanu Firea\"], ''Adev\u0103rul'', September 6, 2010</ref> They have two sons.<ref>{{in lang|ro}} [http://www.mediafax.ro/life-inedit/senatoarea-psd-gabriela-firea-a-nascut-cel-de-al-treilea-baietel-pe-care-il-va-chema-zian-mihail-foto-14210736 \"Senatoarea PSD Gabriela Firea a n\u0103scut cel de-al treilea b\u0103ie\u0163el\"], Mediafax, May 5, 2015</ref>\n\nAt the [[2016 Romanian local election|June 2016 local election]], Firea was elected the first female mayor of Bucharest.<ref>{{in lang|ro}} Ana Maria Laz\u0103r, [http://www.mediafax.ro/politic/gabriela-firea-prima-femeie-primar-a-capitalei-dupa-doar-4-ani-de-cariera-politica-foto-15453280 \"Gabriela Firea \u2013 prima femeie primar a Capitalei dup\u0103 doar 4 ani de carier\u0103 politic\u0103\"], Mediafax, June 8, 2016</ref> She won 43% from the total of only 33% that went to vote. Her closest challengers, [[Nicu\u0219or Dan]] ([[Save Bucharest Union]]) and [[C\u0103t\u0103lin Predoiu]] ([[National Liberal Party (Romania)|National Liberal Party]]), won 30.5% and 11.2% respectively.<ref>{{in lang|ro}} Roxana Preda, [http://www.mediafax.ro/politic/rezultate-finale-alegeri-locale-2016-gabriela-firea-42-97-nicusor-dan-30-52-catalin-predoiu-11-18-toate-contestatiile-respinse-15467482 \"Rezultate finale alegeri locale 2016\"], Mediafax, June 10, 2016</ref>\n\n==Electoral history==\n===Mayor of Bucharest===\n{| class=wikitable width=100%\n! rowspan=2|Election\n! rowspan=2|Affiliation\n! colspan=3|First round\n! colspan=3|Second round\n|-\n!Votes\n!Percentage\n!Position\n!Votes\n!Percentage\n!Position\n|-align=center\n! [[2016 Romanian local election|2016]]\n| {{yes2|'''[[Social Democratic Party (Romania)|PSD]]'''}} || 246,553 || {{Percentage bar|42.97|c={{Social Democratic Party (Romania)/meta/color}}}} || {{color box|Gold|1st}} || bgcolor=lightgrey colspan=3|\n|}\n\n\n==Notes==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|Gabriela Firea}}\n*{{in lang|ro}} [http://gabriela-firea.ro Official site]\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Firea, Gabriela}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1972 births]]\n[[Category:People from Bac\u0103u]]\n[[Category:Members of the Romanian Orthodox Church]]\n[[Category:Romanian journalists]]\n[[Category:Romanian television presenters]]\n[[Category:Social Democratic Party (Romania) politicians]]\n[[Category:Mayors of Bucharest]]\n[[Category:Members of the Senate of Romania]]\n[[Category:Romanian women in politics]]\n[[Category:Women television presenters]]\n[[Category:Spouses of mayors]]\n", "name_user": "Xammer", "label": "safe", "comment": "it is R\u0103svan, not R\u0103zvan (even if it's a more uncommon form)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gabriela_Firea"}
{"title_page": "Michele Civetta", "text_new": "{{more citations needed|date=July 2018}}\n{{Infobox person\n|name=Michele Civetta\n|birth_date=1976\n|birth_place=[[Italy]]\n|death_date=\n|death_place=\n|occupation=Film director, artist\n|spouse={{marriage|[[Asia Argento]]|2008|2013|reason=divorced}}\n|children=Nicola Civetta\n}}\n\n'''Michele Civetta''' is a film director and multi-media artist and founder of [[Quintessence Films]].\n\n==Career==\nMichele Civetta is an Emmy nominated director. Over the years Civetta has directed videos for [[Lou Reed]], [[Sparklehorse]], Edward Sharpe & the Magnetic Zeros, Marracash, Ladytron, [[Yoko Ono]]. Commercials for [[Coca-Cola]], [[Martini vermouth|Martini & Rossi]], [[Cingular Wireless|Cingular wireless]], Badoit mineral water. In 2006 Civetta wrote and directed a musical feature for Sean Lennon's Capitol Records release Friendly Fire.<ref>[http://www.videostatic.com/vs/2006/week40/index.html IN DEPTH: Sean Lennon \"Friendly Fire\"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090602132645/http://www.videostatic.com/vs/2006/week40/index.html |date=2009-06-02 }}</ref> The 50-minute film debuted January 2008 on Mark Cuban's [[HDNet]] channel.{{citation needed|date=June 2018}}\n\nCivetta was preparing a film based on the international bestseller ''[[Coin Locker Babies]]'' that was scheduled to shoot in the summer of 2010 in Thailand and Japan, a co-production between Don Murphy's Angry Films. Production was delayed to 2013; by May of that year, the project had been renamed ''Regular Boy'', and it was listed on [[IMDb]] as being in \"pre-production\".<ref>{{cite web|title=Michele Civetta|url=https://www.imdb.com/name/nm1869948/?ref_=tt_ov_dr|work=IMDB|publisher=IMDb.com, Inc.|accessdate=20 May 2013}}</ref> In 2015 it was reported to be in development again with the same script and director, now starring [[Vincent Gallo]], [[Liv Tyler]], [[Asia Argento]] and [[Sean Lennon]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://movieweb.com/vincent-gallo-liv-tyler-and-asia-argento-up-to-topline-coin-locker-babies/|publisher=[[MovieWeb]]|title=Vincent Gallo, Liv Tyler and Asia Argento up to topline Coin Locker Babies|author=B., Brian|date=March 14, 2005}}</ref>\n\nCivetta and his company Quintessence Films commissioned and produced a series of 42 second short films based on Dreams for 42 Below Vodka/ Bacardi. Some of the filmmakers involved include David Lynch, Kenneth Anger, [[Gaspar Noe]], Sergei Bodrov, Larry Clark, Harmony Korine, and Mike Figgis.<ref>[http://www.odetoazia.com/?p=1169 Asia Argento and Michele Civetta on Cannes Controversy and Porn-y New Work]</ref>\n\nCivetta embarked on a psychedelic surf film for the New York-based label Mexican summer as a collaboration with members of MGMT, Ariel Pink and Connan Mockasin. Shooting began in Nicaragua fall 2014.{{citation needed|date=June 2018}}\n\nCivetta has worked with a wide array of actors including Asia Argento, Brady Corbett, Lindsay Lohan, [[Carrie Fisher]], Devon Aoki, Paz de la Huerta, Burt Young, Grant Morrison and artists from Yoko Ono to Luigi Ontani, Donald Baechler.{{citation needed|date=June 2018}}\n\nIn 2016 Civetta's commercial Halloween Today for NBC was nominated for an Emmy Award.{{citation needed|date=June 2018}}\n\nApril 3, 2020 Mr Civetta's Feature Film [[Agony]] was released via [[Gravitas Ventures]]. A psychological thriller starring [[Asia Argento]], [[Rade Serbedzija]], [[Ninetto Davoli]], [[Monica Guerritore]] and [[Franco Nero]]. The film has received positive critical reception upon its release.\n[https://filmthreat.com/reviews/agony-2020/]</ref>\n\nMr. Civetta is in post production on the upcoming feature film The Gateway, an inner city crime thriller starring [[Bruce Dern]], [[Olivia Munn]] [[Shea Whigham]], [[Frank Grillo]], [[Mark Boone Jr.]], [[Taryn Manning]] and [[Keith David]].\n[https://variety.com/2019/film/news/frank-grillo-taryn-manning-olivia-munn-on-the-gateway-1203202790/]</ref>\n===Music videos===\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n* \"Better Days\" - [[Edward Sharp and the Magnetic Zeros]] (2013)\n* \"Ours\" - [[Asia Argento]] (2013)\n* \"White Elephant\" - [[Ladytron]] (2011)\n* \"Come la Cina\" \u2013 [[Marracash]] (2009)\n* \"Little Fat Baby\" \u2013 [[Sparklehorse]] (2008)\n* \"By the Time I Get Home\" \u2013 [[Grand National (band)|Grand National]] (2007)\n* \"Ecstasy\" \u2013 [[Lou Reed]] (2007)\n* \"Parachute\" \u2013 [[Sean Lennon]] (2007)\n* \"Dead Meat\" \u2013 Sean Lennon (2006)\n* \"Friendly Fire\" \u2013 Sean Lennon (2006)\n* \"Now that I know\" \u2013 [[Shannon McNally]] (2002)\n{{col-end}}\n\n==Personal life==\nCivetta was married to Italian actress [[Asia Argento]], the couple married on August 27, 2008 in [[Arezzo]].<ref>[http://www.simormora.com/matrimonio/asia-argento-sposa-ad-arezzo-michele-civetta/ Asia Argento Weds Film Director Asia Argento sposa ad Arezzo Michele Civetta | Si Mormora]</ref> The couple lived in Rome with their son Nicola Civetta. The couple divorced in 2013.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb name|id=1869948|name=Michele Civetta}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Civetta, Michele}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Italian film directors]]\n[[Category:Place of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:1976 births]]\n", "text_old": "{{more citations needed|date=July 2018}}\n{{Infobox person\n|name=Michele Civetta\n|birth_date=1976\n|birth_place=[[Italy]]\n|death_date=\n|death_place=\n|occupation=Film director, artist\n|spouse={{marriage|[[Asia Argento]]|2008|2013|reason=divorced}}\n|children=Nicola Civetta\n}}\n\n'''Michele Civetta''' is a film director and multi-media artist and founder of [[Quintessence Films]].\n\n==Career==\nMichele Civetta is an Emmy nominated director. Over the years Civetta has directed videos for [[Lou Reed]], [[Sparklehorse]], Edward Sharpe & the Magnetic Zeros, Marracash, Ladytron, [[Yoko Ono]]. Commercials for [[Coca-Cola]], [[Martini vermouth|Martini & Rossi]], [[Cingular Wireless|Cingular wireless]], Badoit mineral water. In 2006 Civetta wrote and directed a musical feature for Sean Lennon's Capitol Records release Friendly Fire.<ref>[http://www.videostatic.com/vs/2006/week40/index.html IN DEPTH: Sean Lennon \"Friendly Fire\"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090602132645/http://www.videostatic.com/vs/2006/week40/index.html |date=2009-06-02 }}</ref> The 50-minute film debuted January 2008 on Mark Cuban's [[HDNet]] channel.{{citation needed|date=June 2018}}\n\nCivetta was preparing a film based on the international bestseller ''[[Coin Locker Babies]]'' that was scheduled to shoot in the summer of 2010 in Thailand and Japan, a co-production between Don Murphy's Angry Films. Production was delayed to 2013; by May of that year, the project had been renamed ''Regular Boy'', and it was listed on [[IMDb]] as being in \"pre-production\".<ref>{{cite web|title=Michele Civetta|url=https://www.imdb.com/name/nm1869948/?ref_=tt_ov_dr|work=IMDB|publisher=IMDb.com, Inc.|accessdate=20 May 2013}}</ref> In 2015 it was reported to be in development again with the same script and director, now starring [[Vincent Gallo]], [[Liv Tyler]], [[Asia Argento]] and [[Sean Lennon]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://movieweb.com/vincent-gallo-liv-tyler-and-asia-argento-up-to-topline-coin-locker-babies/|publisher=[[MovieWeb]]|title=Vincent Gallo, Liv Tyler and Asia Argento up to topline Coin Locker Babies|author=B., Brian|date=March 14, 2005}}</ref>\n\nCivetta and his company Quintessence Films commissioned and produced a series of 42 second short films based on Dreams for 42 Below Vodka/ Bacardi. Some of the filmmakers involved include David Lynch, Kenneth Anger, [[Gaspar Noe]], Sergei Bodrov, Larry Clark, Harmony Korine, and Mike Figgis.<ref>[http://www.odetoazia.com/?p=1169 Asia Argento and Michele Civetta on Cannes Controversy and Porn-y New Work]</ref>\n\nCivetta embarked on a psychedelic surf film for the New York-based label Mexican summer as a collaboration with members of MGMT, Ariel Pink and Connan Mockasin. Shooting began in Nicaragua fall 2014.{{citation needed|date=June 2018}}\n\nCivetta has worked with a wide array of actors including Asia Argento, Brady Corbett, Lindsay Lohan, [[Carrie Fisher]], Devon Aoki, Paz de la Huerta, Burt Young, Grant Morrison and artists from Yoko Ono to Luigi Ontani, Donald Baechler.{{citation needed|date=June 2018}}\n\nIn 2016 Civetta's commercial Halloween Today for NBC was nominated for an Emmy Award.{{citation needed|date=June 2018}}\n\n===Music videos===\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n* \"Better Days\" - [[Edward Sharp and the Magnetic Zeros]] (2013)\n* \"Ours\" - [[Asia Argento]] (2013)\n* \"White Elephant\" - [[Ladytron]] (2011)\n* \"Come la Cina\" \u2013 [[Marracash]] (2009)\n* \"Little Fat Baby\" \u2013 [[Sparklehorse]] (2008)\n* \"By the Time I Get Home\" \u2013 [[Grand National (band)|Grand National]] (2007)\n* \"Ecstasy\" \u2013 [[Lou Reed]] (2007)\n* \"Parachute\" \u2013 [[Sean Lennon]] (2007)\n* \"Dead Meat\" \u2013 Sean Lennon (2006)\n* \"Friendly Fire\" \u2013 Sean Lennon (2006)\n* \"Now that I know\" \u2013 [[Shannon McNally]] (2002)\n{{col-end}}\n\n==Personal life==\nCivetta was married to Italian actress [[Asia Argento]], the couple married on August 27, 2008 in [[Arezzo]].<ref>[http://www.simormora.com/matrimonio/asia-argento-sposa-ad-arezzo-michele-civetta/ Asia Argento Weds Film Director Asia Argento sposa ad Arezzo Michele Civetta | Si Mormora]</ref> The couple lived in Rome with their son Nicola Civetta. The couple divorced in 2013.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb name|id=1869948|name=Michele Civetta}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Civetta, Michele}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Italian film directors]]\n[[Category:Place of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:1976 births]]\n", "name_user": "Imerguttfursaken", "label": "safe", "comment": "updated recent work with citation.", "url_page": "//en.wiki